1. Ona *teži* ka zdravijem načinu života. (She strives for a healthier lifestyle.)
2. Ovaj zadatak je *težak*. (This task is difficult.)
3. Oni *teže* savršenstvu. (They aim for perfection.)
4. Kugla *teži* 1 kilogram. (The ball weighs 1 kilogram.)
5. On *teži* da bude bolji čovek. (He strives to be a better person.)
6. U ovom trenutku *težimo* ka stabilnosti u poslovanju. (At this moment, we are striving for stability in business.)
7. Zemlja *teži* oko 6 triliona tona. (The Earth weighs around 6 trillion tons.)
8. Oni *teže* pobedi u narednom meču. (They aim to win the next match.)
9. Njegovo ponašanje *teži* ka agresiji. (His behavior tends towards aggression.)
10. *Teži* deo posla je završen. (The difficult part of the job is done.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "teži" can have several different meanings, including "strive", "aim", "weigh", "tend towards", and "be difficult". I have provided a variety of example sentences that demonstrate these different meanings.